arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase XI: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
Soil and wash below Locus 4 in the hypocaust room

Locus 5 is a wash layer in the "hypocaust room" below Locus 4 and above earlier dumping layers (Loci 7 and 8). Locus 5 is differentiated by the color of its soil, Munsell 7.5yr 4/4, brown. This locus has a high plaster content and a small amount of pottery inclusions. The texture of the soil is fine silt. This is a sedimentation layer.
5.90 m north south -by- 4.90 m east west.
